parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Brake Failure due to Hydraulic Control Unit (HCU) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the ABS light and brake warning lights illuminate
the vehicle may pulsate or vibrate when braking
and the brake system may malfunction intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid cooling system can cause the engine to shut off without warning while the vehicle is in motion, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The "Stop Safely Now" message appears on the display
the engine shuts off without warning
the red triangle warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid propulsion system can cause the engine to stall or shut down while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine quits or stalls while driving
the vehicle loses power and can only operate on electric power
the service engine wrench light comes on frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the alarm system can cause unnecessary stress and distraction for the driver, potentially leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: without any apparent reason or trigger.
